{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"811b01c4-0d45-410d-82b2-1e9c691a7739","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n**1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)** — MSTest.Sdk gives you the simplest possible project file:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — no `<PackageReference>` items needed. The SDK bundles MSTest, the runner, and code analyzers.\n\n**2. Enable parallel execution** — add a `.runsettings` file at the project root:\n\n```xml\n<!-- my.runsettings -->\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Workers>0</Workers>          <!-- 0 = use all logical processors -->\n      <Scope>MethodLevel</Scope>    <!-- parallelize across methods, not just classes -->\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nWire it up in the csproj (inside `<PropertyGroup>`):\n\n```xml\n<TestRunParameters>my.runsettings</TestRunParameters>\n```\n\nOr pass it at the CLI: `dotnet test -s my.runsettings`\n\n**3. Run database tests sequentially** — use `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;\n\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]   // ← this class runs sequentially, after all parallel tests finish\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Can_Read_Record() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `[DoNotParallelize]` on a **class** ensures all its methods run serially and *not* concurrently with parallel tests.\n- Parallel tests run first; `[DoNotParallelize]` tests run afterward in isolation.\n- If you prefer class-level parallelism only (safer default), change `Scope` to `ClassLevel` — methods within a class then run sequentially while different classes run in parallel.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7b5765e3-7f9c-4ff6-8e97-af2f4b6a878d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository appears to be empty. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk, parallel execution, and sequential test control.","outputTokens":578,"requestId":"5819:183DE:59AC7BB:61A223B:6A033949"},"id":"bfcde8ee-b523-4b8b-afb3-c3dd4fe5aba5","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:29:43.133Z","parentId":"f921e560-0760-4f7b-a00a-2ca85ed24097"}
